definition: to stand/to set up/to establish/to lay down/to draw up/at once/immediately

square/power or involution (math.)/upright/honest/fair and square/direction/side/party (to a contract, dispute etc)/place/method/prescription (medicine)/just when/only or just/classifier for square things/abbr. for square or cubic meter

sentences.english: That pushed inventories 592 billion cubic feet higher than they were at the same time a year ago.
sentences.chinese: 這使得總庫存達到5920億立方米，高於去年同期。

sentences.english: Their deep bucket can usually store about 3-6 cubic meters of earth.
sentences.chinese: 裝載機的深底剷鬥一般可裝載3～6立方米的土壤。

sentences.english: The volume of this box is 10 steres.
sentences.chinese: 這個箱子的體積是10立方米。

sentences.english: You get that out of 1 cubic kilometer of seawater.
sentences.chinese: 你能從一千立方米海水中得到這麼多。

sentences.english: Ahvaz's annual average of PM10s was 372 micrograms per cubic meter.
sentences.chinese: 阿瓦士年均可吸入顆粒物含量爲每立方米372微克。

sentences.english: The reservoir has in storage about 30 million cubic metres.
sentences.chinese: 這座水庫貯水約3000萬立方米。

sentences.english: The bar mirrors this cubic cupola below, with seating on three sides.
sentences.chinese: 酒吧鏡子這立方米以下的沖天爐，三面的座位。

sentences.english: The exploration capacity would hit 1 trillion cubic meters.
sentences.chinese: 勘探能力將突破1萬億立方米的大關。

sentences.english: This outer coffin used up 540 cubic meters of rare wood.
sentences.chinese: 這座木槨一共耗費了540立方米的名貴木材。

sentences.english: One TEU equals about 12 register tons or 34 cubic metres.
sentences.chinese: 一個標箱等於約12註冊噸或34立方米。

sentences.english: This provided 70m cubic meters of granite to add to the island's foundations.
sentences.chinese: 這個70立方米的花崗岩準備注入這個島的地基中。

sentences.english: In West Germany alone, some 400 million cubic meters of rubble was piled up after the war.
sentences.chinese: 單單在西德，戰後的廢墟堆起來約有四億立方米。

sentences.english: And the available volume is on the order of meters cubed.
sentences.chinese: 整個可用的空間體積有立方米的數量級。

sentences.english: Just three years ago, reserves held 40 billion cubic meters of water.
sentences.chinese: 而僅僅三年前，其的貯水量都有400億立方米。

sentences.english: Fermentations are carried out in stainless steel fermentors with volumes up to 400 m3.
sentences.chinese: 發酵都是在不鏽鋼發酵罐出來的量高達400立方米。

sentences.english: The raw materials of 160000 cubic meters will be supplied by the Province.
sentences.chinese: 原料16萬立方米木材由省內提供。
